name: I Am Where / Lilia
description:
Portrait of Lilia

From project "I am where"
The project is about "Touched out syndrome". I ask young mothers where is the place on their bodies where they feel they are they, and where baby didn't touched them a lot.

Lilia said: "My three pregnancies, having children, time, growing up children, my growing up left their mark on my body. My body has changed, the folds that have become a marker, including of these processes, this is the place where my little children have not been, who needed me. I am where these "cracks" in the skin are the most intimate and most personal for me."

2021
